1
00:00:17,958 --> 00:00:19,000
[NAGI]
Nina Wang.

2
00:00:19,083 --> 00:00:22,875
September seventh,
Immigration Era 325.

3
00:00:22,958 --> 00:00:24,333
She was placed
under the protection

4
00:00:24,416 --> 00:00:26,750
of Major Sergey Wang
after being found

5
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:29,750
in the base of
a resistance cell.

6
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,041
[MIKOTO]
Are you the ones who are seeking

7
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:33,083
this Harmonium's power?

8
00:00:34,875 --> 00:00:36,458
Your Highness.

9
00:00:36,541 --> 00:00:38,541
Yes, I know.

10
00:00:38,625 --> 00:00:39,750
Nina Wang.

11
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:43,833
In my name, I hereby
release your powers.

12
00:00:46,958 --> 00:00:48,666
Materialize!

13
00:00:56,458 --> 00:00:58,750
[MIKOTO] Are you the
player or the protector?

14
00:00:58,833 --> 00:00:59,708
Huh?

15
00:00:59,791 --> 00:01:00,833
Huh?

16
00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:04,250
[MIKOTO]
Either way, show me your power!

17
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,291
[gasps]

18
00:01:07,166 --> 00:01:08,708
[NAGI] Nothing is known
about her birth,

19
00:01:08,791 --> 00:01:10,125
or events leading
up to the day

20
00:01:10,208 --> 00:01:12,125
she was placed under
Artai protection.

21
00:01:12,208 --> 00:01:15,000
She likely became part of the
insurgency through kidnapping

22
00:01:15,083 --> 00:01:16,958
or human trafficking.

23
00:01:19,958 --> 00:01:22,166
The player or the protector...

24
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:23,375
Huh.

25
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:29,333
Huh?

26
00:01:37,458 --> 00:01:38,416
[gasps]

27
00:01:54,625 --> 00:01:56,083
How interesting!

28
00:01:56,166 --> 00:01:59,458
I can't believe it!
Too interesting.

29
00:01:59,541 --> 00:02:01,208
Is it a just coincidence?

30
00:02:01,291 --> 00:02:02,333
No!

31
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:06,833
[chuckling]

32
00:02:06,916 --> 00:02:09,250
[cackling]

33
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:11,125
[grunting]

34
00:02:11,208 --> 00:02:12,541
[MIKOTO]
What's wrong with you?

35
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:15,458
Those weak daggers
can't defeat me!

36
00:02:15,541 --> 00:02:17,500
But I'm not weak!

37
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:19,833
[yells]

38
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,791
[MIKOTO groans]

39
00:02:27,791 --> 00:02:29,083
[MIKOTO]
Hm?

40
00:04:01,666 --> 00:04:05,000
[clanging]

41
00:04:05,083 --> 00:04:06,125
[WOMAN 19C]
Attention, everyone!

42
00:04:06,208 --> 00:04:07,166
It's break time!

43
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:08,583
Lunch is served!

44
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:15,958
Hey, Mashiro, you're
fitting in really well!

45
00:04:16,041 --> 00:04:17,000
Meow.

46
00:04:17,083 --> 00:04:19,375
Don't start comparing
me with you.

47
00:04:22,333 --> 00:04:24,708
[MASHIRO]
She's great, isn't she?

48
00:04:24,791 --> 00:04:25,500
Yeah.

49
00:04:25,583 --> 00:04:27,458
She's really cool.

50
00:04:28,916 --> 00:04:31,041
A leader, huh?

51
00:04:37,416 --> 00:04:38,666
Hey, Arika.

52
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:39,791
From now on, what do we--

53
00:04:39,875 --> 00:04:41,708
[MIDORI]
Arika! Mashiro!

54
00:04:41,791 --> 00:04:42,583
Come.

55
00:04:42,666 --> 00:04:44,833
We have something to discuss.

56
00:04:44,916 --> 00:04:47,541
[ARGOS]
Huh. Queen Mashiro, you say?

57
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:48,375
[FIAR]
Yes.

58
00:04:48,458 --> 00:04:49,833
She's in the Aswad Village.

59
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:52,458
She's with a girl who
appears to be her Otome.

60
00:04:52,541 --> 00:04:54,416
[ARGOS] I was thinking
we could get rid of Aswad

61
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,875
when they moved against us.

62
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:56,833
But this is...

63
00:04:56,916 --> 00:04:58,208
Interesting.

64
00:04:58,291 --> 00:04:59,791
Leak this information
to that brat

65
00:04:59,875 --> 00:05:02,041
from Artai over in Fuka Palace.

66
00:05:02,125 --> 00:05:03,958
Yes, Master.

67
00:05:05,291 --> 00:05:06,291
[ARIKA]
What?!

68
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:07,833
Th-That's ridiculous!

69
00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:10,083
You're planning
to attack Cardair?

70
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:13,291
[RAD] They betrayed us,
and we do not forgive traitors.

71
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:15,000
We need to make
that point clear,

72
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:18,583
so we will eliminate Argos
the 14th and his entire family.

73
00:05:18,666 --> 00:05:20,375
[ARIKA]
No way...

74
00:05:20,458 --> 00:05:22,375
Let me hear your answer
from last night.

75
00:05:22,458 --> 00:05:23,541
Huh?

76
00:05:23,625 --> 00:05:27,041
You mean about lending
you our powers?

77
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:29,333
Blood for blood,
blade for blade.

78
00:05:29,416 --> 00:05:32,000
That is one of the
sacred laws of Aswad.

79
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:34,041
No, this isn't right!

80
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,708
Grandma told me that
if you take revenge

81
00:05:35,791 --> 00:05:39,708
for everything done to you,
it doesn't solve anything!

82
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:44,750
You know, <i>she</i> said
exactly the same thing.

83
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:47,083
We're not interested
in finding solutions.

84
00:05:47,166 --> 00:05:49,916
Taking revenge is mainly
for our own protection.

85
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,208
[gasps]

86
00:05:51,291 --> 00:05:53,208
We of the Aswad
are a cursed people

87
00:05:53,291 --> 00:05:55,500
and we will never
forgive anyone.

88
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:57,416
That reputation
has protected us.

89
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:59,791
[ARIKA]
But... that's still not right!

90
00:05:59,875 --> 00:06:00,541
[MAN 21A]
Leader!

91
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:02,083
Yes, what is it?

92
00:06:02,166 --> 00:06:10,541
[REFUGEES chattering]

93
00:06:10,625 --> 00:06:13,666
[RAD] Fortunately, they haven't
noticed any of us yet.

94
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:14,916
Eliminate them.

95
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:15,791
[gasps]

96
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,500
Roger!

97
00:06:17,583 --> 00:06:20,125
Eliminate them?!

98
00:06:20,208 --> 00:06:21,958
They're refugees from Wind City.

99
00:06:22,041 --> 00:06:23,916
[gasps] Please, Leader!

100
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,000
You have to save them!

101
00:06:27,083 --> 00:06:29,041
The rules of Aswad
do not change.

102
00:06:29,125 --> 00:06:31,625
Those who come near
our village must die.

103
00:06:31,708 --> 00:06:34,083
Cardair is already
aware of this place.

104
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:37,000
Can you be sure that this
is not part of a trap?

105
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:39,375
But still, how can you...?

106
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:41,166
Mashiro, tell her!

107
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:43,208
At this rate, they'll all die!

108
00:06:43,291 --> 00:06:45,041
But they're the ones...

109
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,791
Those people... killed Aoi.

110
00:06:50,875 --> 00:06:52,375
[gasps]

111
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:55,708
[MIDORI] Heh. Even their own
queen has given up on them.

112
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:57,166
[MIDORI]
No, now that I think about it,

113
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,666
it's more likely that
they're the ones

114
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:00,541
who gave up on you first.

115
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:02,041
Mashiro!

116
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:04,791
[meows]

117
00:07:04,875 --> 00:07:05,750
[gasps]

118
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:07,250
[RAD]
How fortunate.

119
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,333
Looks like we won't have to get
our hands dirty after all.

120
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:13,916
--[explosions]
--[REFUGEES screaming]

121
00:07:15,875 --> 00:07:16,666
[WOMAN screams]

122
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:18,375
It's a monster!

123
00:07:18,458 --> 00:07:19,791
[REFUGEES screaming]

124
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:21,166
[yelping]

125
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:25,333
Huh?

126
00:07:25,416 --> 00:07:26,666
[RAD]
Don't move.

127
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:31,125
Mashiro!

128
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:32,750
Come on, Mashiro!

129
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,041
[yelping]

130
00:07:34,125 --> 00:07:35,583
Wait, that's...!

131
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:37,083
Drink up. Here.

132
00:07:37,166 --> 00:07:40,083
You'll die if you get
left behind, ya know.

133
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:42,250
Well, it serves her right.

134
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:44,041
[yelps]

135
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:46,750
[whimpers]

136
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,291
[MIMI]
Every time I look at the castle,

137
00:07:48,375 --> 00:07:50,541
I always think the same thing.

138
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:52,500
The Queen can't see us
from way up there!

139
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:55,875
So that's why I decided
I won't look at her either!

140
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:59,041
Oh, Aoi...

141
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:01,041
[AOI]
Everything will be all right.

142
00:08:01,125 --> 00:08:02,708
I have lots of faith in you!

143
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:04,333
I have no doubt that
you will become

144
00:08:04,416 --> 00:08:06,791
a great queen someday,
Miss Mashiro.

145
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:10,291
[MIMI screams]

146
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:11,416
[gasps]

147
00:08:15,125 --> 00:08:16,750
[MASHIRO, RAD grunt]

148
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:17,916
Arika!

149
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,333
Mashiro!

150
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:20,375
[RAD gasps]

151
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:24,458
[ARIKA grunts]

152
00:08:24,541 --> 00:08:26,291
Materialize!

153
00:08:30,166 --> 00:08:31,833
It's up to you, Arika!

154
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:34,750
[MAN 21B screams]

155
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:35,791
[ARIKA yells]

156
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,083
[yells]

157
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:50,291
[yells]

158
00:08:57,250 --> 00:08:59,000
[RAD]
That girl is pretty good.

159
00:08:59,083 --> 00:09:01,125
The Blue Sky Sapphire...

160
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:04,125
Come on, hang in there!

161
00:09:05,583 --> 00:09:07,041
Mimi!

162
00:09:07,125 --> 00:09:08,125
Leader!

163
00:09:08,208 --> 00:09:09,583
It's fine. Let her go.

164
00:09:09,666 --> 00:09:10,791
[MAN 21D]
Go on, then.

165
00:09:10,875 --> 00:09:11,958
[MASHIRO]
Huh?

166
00:09:16,125 --> 00:09:18,125
[MASHIRO panting]

167
00:09:18,208 --> 00:09:19,458
Mashiro!

168
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:21,000
[MAN 21E]
Queen Mashiro?

169
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:22,625
[WOMAN 21B]
No way...

170
00:09:22,708 --> 00:09:24,291
[MAN 21F]
But she's...

171
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:26,291
Mimi!

172
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:29,875
Hang in there!
Don't give up! Mimi!

173
00:09:33,541 --> 00:09:35,958
[SERGEY] These five girls are
the applicants we have so far.

174
00:09:36,041 --> 00:09:39,000
If things play out right, there
should be more volunteers soon.

175
00:09:39,083 --> 00:09:41,125
Very good, but can these
girls be trusted?

176
00:09:41,208 --> 00:09:43,625
You won't have to worry
about that, Your Highness.

177
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,166
From the moment they
first wear the Gem,

178
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:46,583
they become our Otomes.

179
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:49,791
Valkyries will be totally
incapable of betraying us.

180
00:09:49,875 --> 00:09:52,000
[NAGI] So you're saying
you used the same Gem design

181
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:53,666
of that of a Slave?

182
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:56,000
Yes.

183
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:57,666
Well, time is of the essence.

184
00:09:57,750 --> 00:10:00,041
Let's have the Valkyrie Unit
give us a hand now.

185
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:01,416
Yes, sir.

186
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,625
[NAGI] My informants tell me
Mashiro has been found.

187
00:10:03,708 --> 00:10:05,666
But since the report
comes from Cardair,

188
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:07,166
it might not be true.

189
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:08,833
Apparently, Arika is there, too.

190
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:10,041
[gasps]

191
00:10:10,125 --> 00:10:12,083
Of course, the
situation has changed,

192
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:14,000
as we no longer need Arika.

193
00:10:14,083 --> 00:10:16,000
As a matter of fact,
at this point,

194
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:17,583
she's only in our way.

195
00:10:17,666 --> 00:10:18,541
[gasps]

196
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:19,666
[gasps]

197
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:26,833
But...

198
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:30,000
...we still need to get our
hands on Mashiro's song.

199
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:31,375
Think you can catch her?

200
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:33,791
I thought the issue with
the song had been resolved.

201
00:10:33,875 --> 00:10:34,833
[NAGI]
I know.

202
00:10:34,916 --> 00:10:36,500
But if that person
never wakes up,

203
00:10:36,583 --> 00:10:38,291
what are we supposed to do then?

204
00:10:38,375 --> 00:10:40,375
Yes, but still...

205
00:10:40,458 --> 00:10:42,291
Let me go instead!

206
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,166
Afraid I can't let you.

207
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,375
But...

208
00:10:45,458 --> 00:10:48,291
[NAGI]
Tsk, tsk, tsk. Nope.

209
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:50,625
Your Highness, I, Sergey Wang,

210
00:10:50,708 --> 00:10:53,000
will complete this
mission flawlessly.

211
00:10:53,083 --> 00:10:54,041
--[NINA gasps]
--[NAGI] Huh?

212
00:10:54,125 --> 00:10:55,541
[SERGEY]
Nina, don't worry about me.

213
00:10:55,625 --> 00:10:58,375
I have been a part of Artai's
military since I was born.

214
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:00,041
This is what I was meant to do.

215
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:01,500
But, Father...

216
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:07,750
So you just concentrate
on fulfilling your duties.

217
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:09,708
Protect His Highness,
the Grand Duke,

218
00:11:09,791 --> 00:11:12,125
as his Meister Otome, Nina.

219
00:11:12,208 --> 00:11:13,416
Yes.

220
00:11:17,916 --> 00:11:20,333
We've gathered almost
all the cards.

221
00:11:20,416 --> 00:11:22,916
Now, when we finally do
obtain the last key,

222
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,916
how should I use that thing?

223
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,375
The power of technology...

224
00:11:28,458 --> 00:11:30,958
[NAGI] Will it lead us down
a path of destruction,

225
00:11:31,041 --> 00:11:34,250
or towards a bright
future for humanity?

226
00:11:35,625 --> 00:11:39,166
[NAGI] But, no matter what, the
ending is not for you to decide.

227
00:11:41,583 --> 00:11:45,250
Isn't that right...
so-called Predecessor?

228
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:53,750
As I pray to you,
I can't help remembering

229
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:56,916
the words of that girl,
Arika Yumemiya.

230
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,416
"If Otomes are friends,
then why must they

231
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:02,625
be forced to kill each other?
I will never do such a thing,

232
00:12:02,708 --> 00:12:04,958
and I will never allow
that to happen."

233
00:12:05,041 --> 00:12:06,666
I could not tell her,
but that's something

234
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:08,833
I've been secretly
searching for,

235
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:12,500
and something that every
Otome desires in her heart.

236
00:12:12,583 --> 00:12:14,708
I feel the same, however,

237
00:12:14,791 --> 00:12:18,416
conflicts are inevitable as long
as there are nations and people.

238
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:24,291
[YUKARIKO] That's why this
world has to be steered

239
00:12:24,375 --> 00:12:25,958
from the path of destruction.

240
00:12:26,041 --> 00:12:27,666
That's why Our Lady
decided that--

241
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:29,375
I know that. In fact...

242
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:31,541
I know that all too well.

243
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:33,666
It's because of that ideal
that we have sent out

244
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:37,208
so many of our students
and sacrificed their lives.

245
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:42,500
[MARIA] And yet, after all that,
the only thing I can do

246
00:12:42,583 --> 00:12:44,666
is stay here and pray.

247
00:12:47,041 --> 00:12:48,500
Miss Maria...

248
00:12:48,583 --> 00:12:53,500
If you don't mind, will you
allow me to pray alongside you?

249
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:56,500
Even if we pray, it won't
solve anything, you know.

250
00:12:56,583 --> 00:12:57,375
I know that.

251
00:12:57,458 --> 00:12:59,708
But still... It's something.

252
00:13:05,416 --> 00:13:08,416
[TOMOE] I have to go and find
Queen Mashiro and Arika now.

253
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,208
If I manage to succeed,

254
00:13:10,291 --> 00:13:12,250
I'll put in a request
to His Highness,

255
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:15,000
and ask about freeing
the Headmistress for you.

256
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:17,625
Don't worry yourself,
I'll be waitin' here patiently.

257
00:13:17,708 --> 00:13:21,041
Goo-goo, ga-ga. Goo-goo.

258
00:13:21,125 --> 00:13:23,916
You're... embarrassing
me, Big Sister.

259
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:27,000
Please forget what
happened today.

260
00:13:27,083 --> 00:13:29,291
[door thuds]

261
00:13:31,708 --> 00:13:35,458
[SHIZURU] For the time bein',
I'll let you do as you wish.

262
00:13:35,541 --> 00:13:36,750
But...

263
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:42,291
I must admit,
I kinda had fun today.

264
